label_mapping.label: auto_net_score
label_mapping.description: The total number of game pieces scored by a robot into the 'Net' scoring area during the autonomous period of a match. This metric reflects the robot's autonomous scoring effectiveness specifically for the Net target.
label_mapping.typical_range: 0-5 (may vary depending on game rules and scoring opportunities)
label_mapping.usage_context: Track this metric during the autonomous period by counting each game piece successfully scored by the robot into the Net. Record immediately after autonomous ends, based on observed scoring or official field data.

label_mapping.label: driver_skill_rating
label_mapping.description: Number of observed driver errors or notable driving maneuvers during the match.
label_mapping.usage_context: Scouted live during each match by counting visible driver mistakes or impressive actions, such as quick recoveries, precise alignment, or evasive maneuvers.

label_mapping.label: strategy_field
label_mapping.description: Briefly describes the primary strategies a team employed on the field during the match.
label_mapping.usage_context: Scouted live during matches to capture notable strategic approaches or shifts observed for each team.

label_mapping.label: scout_comments
label_mapping.description: Free-form notes for recording observations or strategic insights about a team's performance during a match.
label_mapping.usage_context: Entered by scouts during or immediately after a match to capture details not covered by other metrics, such as unique strategies, robot issues, or alliance interactions.
